Problem Details:
Greetings Support,
                       One of our HCS customer is facing issue with Cisco Jabber MRA point to point calls with Video Endpoints like DX80, MX300, Spark room kit and MX800. The issue is that the call connect and only video is seen at both ends but no audio at either ends. We need your kind assistance to resolve the issue.
Subject: No Audio, just video on Cisco Jabber MRA and TP Endpoints Calls
Sub Technology: Collaboration Edge / Mobile and Remote Access (MRA)
Resolution Summary:
CU fixed the issue be changing the video bandwidth settings but the issue didn't lie either on Jabber  or any other HCS component. 
According to the captures collected on the end point (Jabbber) and on the ASA, the RTP stream was leaving the client but it was not reaching the HCS infrastructure so there was some drops on the ISP due to the bandwidth usage.

Problem Details:
Customer called in stating that they have issues with apple push notifications,
production loss is there, Business impact is there.
tried troubleshooting but did not help.
Subject: JAB-IPH-HCS-RTU//Not receiving the notifications.
Technology: Voice - Communications Manager Additional Apps and Plugins
Sub Technology: Presence Server (CUPS) - (APNS) Apple Push Notification
Resolution Summary:
Switching to cisco-uds DNS SRV records resolved the issue



---

I am seeing in the log that the signout is being triggered after the Jabber is discovering new presence servers and prompting to sign out:


2020-01-06 11:06:05,471 INFO  [0x000000016fa37000] [src/dnsutils/apple/appleDnsUtils.cpp(30)] [csf.dns] [logResult] - *-----* DNS query _cuplogin._tcp.autonation.com. has succeeded.
2020-01-06 11:06:05,472 INFO  [0x000000016fa37000] [-diagnostics/src/DiagnosticsImpl.cpp(50)] [csf.diagnostics] [AddRecord] - Add record task enqueued: _cuplogin._tcp.autonation.com.

2020-01-06 11:06:05,477 INFO  [0x0000000107309800] [nfigChangedConnectorManagerImpl.cpp(140)] [IMPServices] [askSignOutAndSignIn] - PresenceServerAddress changed requires sign out and sign in

2020-01-06 11:06:05,895 INFO  [0x0000000107309800] [/login/YLCMockUILifeCycleMannager.m(176)] [UI.Action.System] [-[YLCMockUILifeCycleMannager signOut]] - jabber start signout

This is happening due to the nature of the additional discovery with CUPLOGIN SRV records in place, which causes a change to the currently used IM&P server and results in us being prompted to sign out and sign back in.

Currently you are not utilizing cisco-uds records:

2020-01-06 10:58:27,407 WARN  [0x000000017040f000] [src/dnsutils/apple/appleDnsUtils.cpp(26)] [csf.dns] [logResult] - *-----* DNS query _cisco-uds._tcp.autonation.com. has failed (QUERY_FAILED).


It is suggested to use _cisco-uds SRV records as there are no mention to configuring the cuplogin records in the On Prem Deployment guides:

 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/jabber/12_5/DIG_OnPrem/cjab_b_on-premises-deployment-cisco-jabber_125/cjab_b_on-premises-deployment-cisco-jabber_125_chapter_01101.html?bookSearch=true#CJAB_TK_C3219F67_00

Resolution Summary:
It was suggested this:

++ utils dbreplication stop on UCCX sub then on pub.
++ utils dbreplication dropadmindb first on UCCX sub then on pub.
++ utils dbreplication reset all from UCCX pub.


After applied that CU had:


admin:utils dbreplication runtimestate
 
Server Time: Thu Jan  2 04:15:23 EST 2020

SERVER-NAME         IP ADDRESS        (msec)    DbMon?    Group ID       (RTMT) & Details
-----------         ----------        ------    -------   -----------    ------------------
kctcsccb            10.128.254.147    0.379     Y/Y/Y     (-)            (4) Setup Failed
kctcscca            10.128.254.146    0.011     Y/Y/Y     (g_2)          (2) Setup Completed

Was provided this, to rebuild: ?utils dbreplication rebuild all?

After that, it was working, however, CDS and HDS were not:

"Enabling of subscriber config datastore and historical datastore Failed: Config Controller for CRS Config Datastore on node 2 : can not execute enable() because node 2 is not active"

Was found this possible bug:

 https://bst.cloudapps.cisco.com/bugsearch/bug/CSCut51198


And suggested:

-       Stopp the DB replication on both the nodes, followed by a restart of DB replication reset all.
 
-       Try to ping and SSH subscriber using publisher and vice a versa.
 
-       From the UCCX Publisher all the subscribers service should still shown unknown while the Publisher service all shows ?IN SERVICE?
 
-       Reboot the UCCX Publisher followed by the Subscriber
 
-       Try to enable HDS/CDS from publisher , verify if we have any error
 
-       Reset the application from GUI  , enable HDS/CDS , check if  all Subscriber  service shows ?IN SERVICE?


After some days, CU agreed with closure.

59010458.007 |22:15:15.237 |AppInfo  |Digit analysis: analysis results
59010458.008 |22:15:15.237 |AppInfo  ||PretransformCallingPartyNumber=
|CallingPartyNumber=
|DialingPartition=Cu1-DirNum-PT
|DialingPattern=63280151
|FullyQualifiedCalledPartyNumber=+918037980151
|DialingPatternRegularExpression=(63280151)
 
 
We discovered it was a configuration issue, since the non-working call was being routed to the SME, which was not correct. We discovered that there was an ILS route that was being learned from CL47.
 
So to fix this we went to the CSS and added Cu1-DirNum-PT in the CSS and moved the learned partition to the last place (Cu1-PreISR-PT) so it didn?t had much priority.
After changing this in the CUCM, all calls started to work for all the users that had the issue.
 
As agreed I?ll proceed and close this ticket.

Problem Details:
We are running UCCE version 11.5.1 and have been running into an issue with the AW+HDS Servers running at over 98% CPU and at times locking up due to high CPU utilization. In reviewing these Server's we noticed that the SQL Profiler shows that the highest reads and writes and in turn CPU load was coming from the CCDM application (Cisco Contact Center Domain Manager). We are not sure if this is a coincidence or related but this CPU overload issue on the Cisco AWHDS Servers also started after we resolved an issue with CCDM that quit working. We had opened a case with Cisco TAC to resolve the CCDM issue as it turned out that CCDM database had filled up the Disk and eGain along with TAC had us increase the disk size for the CCDM Database which we did and this resolved the CCDM issue, but right after this the UCCE AWHDS A side server started showing High CPU utilization and locked up and we had to reboot the server as CUIC Reports couldn't be run. Once we rebooted the A side AWHDS server, the CUIC reports were working again but now the B side AWHDS started showing High CPU the very next day. This prompted us to review the SQL profiler on the B side Server and found that a lot of the Connections and read/write cycles were coming from CCDM. 

We will need TAC assistance to get to the bottom of this issue and help resolve the same.
Subject: UCCE 11.5 - Side B AW/HDS server CPU overload issue
Sub Technology: UCCE/Contact Center Enterprise/ICM - Hosted Collaboration Solution (HCS)
Resolution Summary:
*   You had previously increased the CPU allocation/reservation of the AW servers on side A and B to 5000 MHz and the RAM to 16 GB.
  *   You had identified that the process consuming most of the CPU was SQL server.
  *   We then proceeded to run ?Reports>>Standard Reports>>Performance ? Top Queries by Average CPU Time?
  *   The report was not clear so we ran the following SQL query to confirm the longest running query.
     *   SELECT p.spid, p.status, p.hostname, p.loginame, p.cpu, r.start_time, t.text FROM sys.dm_exec_requests as r, master.dbo.sysprocesses as p CROSS APPLY sys.dm_exec_sql_text(p.sql_handle) t WHERE p.status NOT IN ('sleeping', 'background') AND r.session_id = p.spid
     *   SELECT sqltext.TEXT, req.session_id, req.status, req.command, req.cpu_time, req.total_elapsed_time FROM sys.dm_exec_requests req CROSS APPLY sys.dm_exec_sql_text(sql_handle) AS sqltext
  *   We found a long running query using most CPU
  *   [cid:image001.png@01D5CFAD.079254E0]
  *   We proceeded to kill the query with ?KILL 364? and CPU dropped to 1% immediately.
  *   We identified the query as a custom report developed by your customer on CUIC.

Problem Details:
Hello,

We have a doubt regarging the LocalQTime field in the Termination Call Detail. First, our deployment is  a comprehensive call flow deployment and the flow is :

PSTN>CUBE>CVP>ICM routes and finds a label>Send label to CVP>CUCM to answer call.

We use a Queue to skill group node to queue calls and use the Run Ext. Script node to play music on hold.

If i spend 30 seconds waiting for an agent to be available, this duration is reported in the NetQTime field and LocalQTime is 0. The DB Schema is not very clear or seems contradictory and we cannot find anything on anywhere to clarify this.

We are running version 11.5
Subject: LocalQTime vs NetQTime in Termination Call Detail
Sub Technology: UCCE/Contact Center Enterprise/ICM - Admin Workstation/Distributor/HDS
Resolution Summary:
To have the LocalQTime populated you need to reconfigure the VRU PIM with ?Queue reporting?

NetQTime = total time on Network VRU
LocalQTime = : During its duration, a call can be queued to multiple answering resources(for example, a trunk, voice port, skill group, etc.). LocalQTime includes time the callspent queued to any of these resources

Problem Details:
UCM Version 11.5.1.16900-16

We have had issues over the past month where we have had to reboot our UCM server to fix an issue with getting calls to a fax server.  The call flow is that calls either internally or over the PSTN go to our SME cluster and use a SIP trunk to reach the fax server.  When it starts failing we always receive a busy signal.  The cluster is made of a publisher and 2 subscribers.  I first tried resetting the SIP trunk which did not help.  I restarted the Call Manager services on all 3 servers and it did not fix the issue. Based on the logs provided it was a communication issue between cucm and the IP 10.10.20.25.

For further reoccurrences, we can disable options ping from the fax server sip-trunk to confirm the communication issue with 10.10.20.25.

If the options pings are disabled we will see multiples invites being sent by CUCM to the fax server without any response.

Subject: SOLUTION SUPPORT - 19507 - Cisco CallManager TFTP File Detection (CCM Devices)
Sub Technology: Communications Manager Event Log Errors / Alarms
Resolution Summary:
This is the vulnerability or CVE which you are looking for :
 https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2013-7030

Please note this is a disputed advisory as TFTP is an essential part of the architecture and is working as design.
Cisco didn't request this CVE-ID and we dispute that it is even a vulnerability.  It is service detection.
A mitigation already exists to safeguard against the potential for information disclosure as a result of this design, by using encrypted TFTP Phone configuration files, which can be enabled via the following:
   https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/cucm/security/11_5_1/secugd/CUCM_BK_SEE2CFE1_00_cucm-security-guide-1151/CUCM_BK_SEE2CFE1_00_cucm-security-guide-1151_chapter_01011.pdf

I hope this information helps.

Problem Details: We will need to logout certain mobility profiles every day after business hours ? will need to exclude some profiles . Is this possible from CUCM or CUCDM  ? or what options do we have?
Subject: CUCM: Logout certain mobility profiles every day after business hours
Sub Technology: Communications Manager Extension Mobility
Resolution Summary:
I checked with VOSS engineer and they don't have this option. 

From CUCM:

From Cisco Unified CM administration page go to -- > Bulk Administration -- > Phones -- > Update Phones -- > Query
 
       In this list you can either choose one phone or a set of phones from the search to force the log out ( choose one phone for testing purposes, and choose all  when you want to set the settings for all phones)
 
       Press next, in this page we don?t want to change anything ( we only want to create an empty query just to force the phones to logout from EM) check the picture below:
 
 
A screenshot of a cell phone

Description automatically generated
 
 
       mark to logout users before update and don?t reset/restart/apply config ( we don?t want to affect the phone we just want to logout)
 
       Press submit
 
       Go to Bulk Administration --- > Job Scheduler
 
       Find the job you just created  (check the Submit Date Time<javascript:onColumnFindSubmit(%22batjob.submitdatetime%22,%22true%22)> to find which one)
 
       In that Job scheduler configure the following ( as seen below)
 
A screenshot of a cell phone

Description automatically generated
 
       In the scheduled Date Time choose time to match 18:00:00 ( if your system clock is different than the phone clock, make sure to make the appropriate adjustments to match 6 PM)
 
       In frequency choose daily.
 
       Save and activate Job.



Another option could be using APIs:
 
https://developer.cisco.com/docs/extension-mobility-api/#!overview/overview

Problem Details: Is there any way to find our or generate a report if user is not logged in for certain days ? for ex 45 days
Subject: CUCM: Extension mobility report.
Sub Technology: Hosted Collaboration Solution (HCS) - (Solution Support Contract Required)
Resolution Summary:
I did some research regarding your request. In short it?s not possible to get this information precisely.
 
Some information is stored in DB but it?s per Phone and not EM  profile. So in some cases you can?t say for sure.
 
However you can find these information useful:
 
Getting EM information from Cisco Unified Reporting.
 
CUCM allows to get some information from reporting:
 
A screenshot of a cell phone

Description automatically generated
 
However it provides very limited information. We can see some basic information like number of phones with EM enabled, logged in users etc. 
 
Getting additional information using SQL.
 
EM related information is stored in a "extensionmobilitydynamic" table. It's important to understand that raws are created  in it when you enable EM on a device ( phone etc.):
 
 
 
So if we want to count all the devices in that table you can run : 
 
admin:run sql select count(*) from extensionmobilitydynamic
(count(*))
==========
30     
 
If we want to see all devices we can do:
 
admin:run sql select dv.name from extensionmobilitydynamic emd inner join device dv on emd.fkdevice = dv.pkid
name            
===============
SEPB678AC554336
SEP001C58FB055D
SEP655645765765
MARIO           
SEP04FE7F688D5C
....
 
Or search for a specific one: 
 
admin:run sql select dv.name from extensionmobilitydynamic emd inner join device dv on emd.fkdevice = dv.pkid where dv.name == 'SEPE8B74837E3C3'
name            
===============
SEPE8B74837E3C3
 
If we want to get similar output to a CUCM gui report with all logged in users we can run: 
 
admin:run sql select eu.userid,DBINFO('utc_to_datetime', emd.logintime) as logintime,emd.loginduration, dv.name from extensionmobilitydynamic emd inner join device dv on emd.fkdevice = dv.pkid inner join enduser eu on emd.fkenduser = eu.pkid
userid logintime             loginduration name            
====== ===================== ============= ===============
alex   2018-03-20 11:48:07.0 0             SEPE8B74837E3C3
 
One important thing is that fkenduser contains enduser pkid when user is logged in. When user is not logged in into a phone it's set to NULL :
 
admin:run sql select dv.name , emd.fkenduser from extensionmobilitydynamic emd inner join device dv on emd.fkdevice = dv.pkid
name            fkenduser                            
=============== ====================================
SEPE8B74837E3C3 ee495db1-74f1-31f2-4a1c-6e1a6930a7cc
SEP001E4AF0DBDA NULL                                 
SEP001C58FB055D NULL
 
Another important information is fkenduser_lastlogin and datetimestamp. We  can get infromation about the last user logged in to a phone. Also we can get a timestamp. 
 
admin:run sql select eu.userid,DBINFO('utc_to_datetime', emd.datetimestamp) as datetimestamp, dv.name from extensionmobilitydynamic emd inner join device dv on emd.fkdevice = dv.pkid inner join enduser eu on emd.fkenduser_lastlogin = eu.pkid
userid datetimestamp         name            
====== ===================== ===============
alex   2018-03-20 12:10:25.0 SEPE8B74837E3C3
drv    2016-02-23 00:04:30.0 SEP503DE57D7812
 
datetimestamp specifies logout date and time. This information is updated only when user logs out. So you can see different users for currently logged in and the last logged out. 
 
Understanding limitations of SQL infromation from extentionmobilitydynamic table.
 
Some customers would like to identify users which didn't use EM for a long time. It can't be done because if we don't see a user logged in or we don't see a user logged out it doesn't mean that he is not using EM. This table is based on devices with EM enabled. So here is example: 
 
User1 logs in to a Phone1
User1 logs out from Phone1 
User2 logs in to Phone1
User2 logs out from Phone1 
 
So we don't see any infromation related to User1 using EM on a Phone1.

Requested below information

What is the Complete CUC Version?

        Please go to Cisco Unity Connection Administration page.
o   Go to Telephony integrations>> Port group >> Click on Port group and send me a screenshot of this page.
       
Did you start receiving this alert after upgrading the CUC to 11.5.1SU6 or higher version? yes
When did this alert start getting generated? From yesterday
Did you perform any upgrade? Yes
Are you getting this alert on both the nodes or only 1? Only on PUB
Could you please share the snippet of the complete Alert that you received on RTMT?
  
How frequently are you seeing this alert? Daily 2 times
What is the business impact? NO Impact as of now

######

I did some research on this. That is an alert from RTMT, the Appid CuLicMgrSvr is for license issue and the Alarm type CucStopEncryption is for encryption.
 
The issue seems to be due to export control feature functionality which appears from unity connection 11.5 SU3 onwards, the RTMT alert was added from SU6 version. Hence if you have recently upgraded the CUC to 11.5.1SU6 or higher version , would explains why the issue appeared after the upgrade.
 
Please take a look to the following documentation:
 
   https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/connection/11x/security/b_11xcucsecx/b_11xcucsecx_chapter_01011.html
 
You can safely ignore the alert if you're not using encryption on your unity connection cluster (as secure integration SCCP or SIP). There's no any bug documented about this behaviour since is it a new feature that appeared on 11.5's most recent releases and not an issue with previous versions.

This service should be active when MFT is configured. We verified that you have Peer to Peer file transfer configured. According to this guide:

This service can only starts if an external database and an external file server have been assigned, and if the service can connect to the database and mount the file server.

Problem Details:
Hello Cisco TAC,

Our customer is having trouble receiving calls on their main number 418-228-8953.  They have users configured within a hunt list.  When dialing the main line number 418-228-8953 the calls are not routing to the users.
I did block the translation pattern for a test and confirmed the calls are hitting the Call Manager by receiving an error recording (I have reverted the block). 

I placed a test call this morning at 0927am CT from 847-228-5120 to 418-228-8953.  I will upload the log file to the TAC case.  Please let me know if you can do a WebEX ASAP so I can share the setup.

Thank you
Subject: 273048175.Nortrax-John Deere.Call is not routing to Hunt List 418-228-8953
Sub Technology: Communications Manager PSTN/PBX Inbound/outbound Call Routing (Route pattern, Translation pattern, CSS, etc)
Resolution Summary:
Factory restart of reception device corrected initial issue.
After this only the reception device was ringing, no other device in line group was ringing.

Translation Pattern was not pointing to the specific hunt pilot number. It was configured to point to the specific reception number (61600).
We changed the pattern to point to 61681 (hunt pilot). This allowed all devices in the line group to ring.

Subject: [VF][HCS][SMG&LICTP] Jabber calls drop if remote party sends re-INVITE
Sub Technology: Communications Manager PSTN/PBX Inbound/outbound Call Failure across Cisco Gateway (H.323, MGCP, SIP)
Resolution Summary:
Workaround is to use region configuration.

BU final analysis below:

We discussed with the team and see the CUCM behavior is proper and works as designed.

During mid call, when we receive offer from one leg, the region bandwidth is checked and not the location bandwidth.  Location bandwidth is not reserved unless really needed. As per the LBM design, we check for Location CAC only after we receive the capabilities from both ends. This way, the bandwidth is not blocked or wasted unnecessarily.

Elaborating on it more, Let?s assume if bandwidth is allocated during 200ok itself, and it takes a few seconds to get the other end capabilities and finally if it responds without video caps, then we are unnecessarily blocking the bandwidth for few seconds.

One more use case is, if we try to allocate the bandwidth during offer itself and if it?s not available at that point of time, then video lines will not be included at all.

The rationale behind this design is to delay the bandwidth allocation as much as possible and allocate it if and only when needed so that it?s not blocked for other calls.

During early offer, location bandwidth is checked initially itself since we are still in process of setting up the call.

Hope this clarifies customer query.

Problem Details: Outbound call failure between CUCM node and CUBE-SP
Subject: Outbound Call Failure
Sub Technology: Communications Manager PSTN/PBX Inbound/outbound Call Routing (Route pattern, Translation pattern, CSS, etc)
Resolution Summary:
The root cause for the outage is the same root cause as described in CSCuw41476.  In this outage, the network error occurred to the SIP stack sending a SIP message at the same instance the ethernet port is shut for the DNS changes.  The software fix for CSCuw41476 is to re-open the port after the 1 minute timer.  This fix did not resolve this issue because when the system tried to re-open the port after the 1 minute timer, the re-open also failed.  This leaves the system with the same symptoms as CSCuw41476.  The re-open appears to fail because a 2nd DNS change is occurring at this same time.  I would describe this as a double failure condition.

Please make sure the script that does the DNS changes waits at least 2 minutes between changes to allow the fix for CSCuw41476 to recover the UDP port.
 CSCvj52834 is an enhancement request which suggests not closing the port at all after a send failure.  This enhancements also suggests using TCP as a workaround to avoid the hitting the root cause for CSCuw41476.

Resolution Summary:
Actions Taken / Troubleshooting Done:
*************************************
- Requested Eventviewer logs for the CUCM cluster.
- Found that CDR file parse was failing because the username associated with the phone has a comma in it.

callingPartyUnicodeLoginUserID
VARCHAR(128)
Mex (A), Switzerland

- Got into a WebEx with customer and fixed all BadCDRFiles removing the commas from them, restarted the CDR services (Repository Manager and Agent),

Problem Details:
Hi,

A few weeks ago I noticed that the HCMF 11.5.4 did not generated any SI files anymore (no scheduled, and no ondemand SI reports). 

Therefor I have done the following steps first to try to solve the issue:
- Restart SI service via CLI (service was running, but restarted it anyway and tried a new ondemand report, still failing)
- Reboot the HCMF server (ondemand reports still failing after that)
- Upgrade HCMF server to latest 11.5.5ES1 version (encountered a problem that no switch version was possible)
- Rebuild complete HCMF 11.5.4 server, restored backup, and upgraded successful to 11.5.5ES1

So the HCMF is now up&running with 11.5.5ES1 (11.5.5.11001-1) version.

Unfortunately in 11.5.5ES1 the SI files are still not generated properly.

For the 10.6.3 report type the job does not generate any SI files at all, and the job fails after a long time (>2h)

I have checked that all services are up&running.
Attached some screenshots.

Regards, Chris

If your vTPS's are on 4.3 or later:

Option 1 (Recommended)

  3.  Disable multiparty licensing for TelePresence Servers

Problem Details:
IBM IGA Extension Mobility Functionality Questions
a) We are changing IP address for EM Phone service currently Publisher IP address - from IP Address to FQDN with FQDN returning Sub 1 and Sub 2 IP address.  This is to provide redundancy To test redundancy is it fine to stop Call Manager and EM service on S1 and see EM login prevails? This is the way we tested in a test cluster and it seem to work. 
b) When S1 has Call Manager and EM service stooped is there any SQL query or visual indication that phones are using FQDN and using S2 for service
b1) How long does it take for S1 to S2 failover when we have large number of devices on a subscriber like 5000 - how many minutes it takes? 
c) Unrelated to EM redundancy topic we have the need to change the name of the phone service. If I change the service name and do update subscription the cucm 11.5 does not update it on the phones and UDPs. For example if I change the name Extension Mobility Local to Extension Mobility 7937/40/60 and click update subscriptions the phones and UDPs retain the old phone Extension Mobility. Do you know if this is a bug or is there a way to correct it?
d) If I delete the EM Phone service I tested to find it gets de-subscribed then if I re-subscribe with the correct name it works - is this procedure OK
e) We have the need all UDPs with 2 services (Extension Mobility for EMCC for newer phones and EM for old phones 7937/40/60) in that correct order. We have a mix of UDPs with no service, one service, incorrect name etc. Is the best approach delete the service and create a udp template with 2 services (with correct name and correct order) and resubscribe? In my test cluster this works
Subject: IBM IGA Extension Mobility Functionality Questions
Sub Technology: Communications Manager Extension Mobility
Resolution Summary:
IBM IGA Extension Mobility Functionality Questions
a) We are changing IP address for EM Phone service currently Publisher IP address - from IP Address to FQDN with FQDN returning Sub 1 and Sub 2 IP address.  
This is to provide redundancy To test redundancy is it fine to stop Call Manager and EM service on S1 and see EM login prevails? 
This is the way we tested in a test cluster and it seem to work. 

Answer/ It is OK to stop CUCM service as long as other registered phones are not been affected

b) When Sub1 has Call Manager and EM service stooped is there any SQL query or visual indication that phones are using FQDN and using S2 for service
Answer/ there is not SQL query but you can use the RTMT tool to check how many phones are registered to each SUB in the cluster.

b1) How long does it take for S1 to S2 failover when we have large number of devices on a subscriber like 5000 - how many minutes it takes? 
Answer/ The time is deterine by few factors, how many registration request the TFTP server will handle at same time and how quick the network is for the phones to reach the CUCM cluster.

c) Unrelated to EM redundancy topic we have the need to change the name of the phone service. 
If I change the service name and do update subscription the cucm 11.5 does not update it on the phones and UDPs. 
For example if I change the name Extension Mobility Local to Extension Mobility 7937/40/60 and click update subscriptions the phones and UDPs retain the old phone Extension Mobility. 
Do you know if this is a bug or is there a way to correct it? 
Answer/ for that kind of change you need to recreate the phone service and re-subscribe the phones to the service.

d) If I delete the EM Phone service I tested to find it gets de-subscribed then if I re-subscribe with the correct name it works - is this procedure OK 
Answer/ that is correct, it is the right procedure.

e) We have the need all UDPs with 2 services (Extension Mobility for EMCC for newer phones and EM for old phones 7937/40/60) in that correct order. 
We have a mix of UDPs with no service, one service, incorrect name etc. Is the best approach delete the service and create a udp template with 2 services (with correct name and correct order) and resubscribe? 
In my test cluster this works

Answer/ that is correct way to do it.

Problem Details:
we have 34 Webex Roomkits registered to an HCS CUCM. these endpoints are not providing CMR stats to the CUCM.

in the CAR table all stats show as Null for packet lost/Jitter/MOS Score.
Subject: Webex Roomkit registered to HCS CUCM not providing CMR Stats for calls.
Technology: Voice - Communications Manager Additional Apps and Plugins
Sub Technology: Communications Manager CDR Admin Tool (CAR)
Resolution Summary:
Hitting below defect. 

Defect: CSCub07733, Update CMR records for calls from sip trunks
 https://bst.cloudapps.cisco.com/bugsearch/bug/CSCub07733/?reffering_site=dumpcr

Symptom:
Update CMR records for calls from sip endpoints & sip trunks

Conditions:
Currently there are no CMR records generated when calls are made from sip endpoints or when calls pass through a sip trunk, raising this product enhancement request so that we can get support for this feature.

Workaround:
NA

Further Problem Description:
Newer phone SIP FWs can provide call statistics but there will be no CMR / call statistics from a SIP Trunk.

When the SIP GW supports it, the SIP GW / PSTN can send RTP statistics when sending the BYE message, but since the SIP trunk destination may or may not generate these, this feature, (CMR records), was not extended to SIP Trunks.

In case the SIP Trunk destination supports RTP statistics, you should see on the BYE message something like:

CSeq: 102 BYE
Reason: Q.850;cause=16
Max-Forwards: 68
P-RTP-Stat: PS=294,OS=47040,PR=308,OR=48344,PL=0,JI=0,LA=0,DU=6
Content-Length: 0


Call Detail Records Administration Guide for Cisco Unified Communications Manager, Release 11.5(1)
 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/cucm/service/11_5_1/cdrdef/cucm_b_cucm-cdr-administration-guide-1151/cucm_b_cucm-cdr-administration-guide-1151_chapter_01001.html


## Below devices support CMR.



[cid:image001.png@01D5D751.66DD7550]



Please check out the following white paper:

Cisco Prime Collaboration Assurance and Analytics: Grade VoIP Calls using SCSR Instead of MOS White Paper
 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/products/collateral/cloud-systems-management/prime-collaboration/white-paper-c11-735409.html


"For phones that do not generate CMR, such as Cisco TelePresence(r) TC, CE, CTX, and IX endpoints; Jabber(r) platforms (all platforms); Cisco IP Communicator; and Cisco Unified Personal Communicator, grading will be "N/A"."


So basically, telepresence endpoints do not support call management record in CUCM and doesn't send call statistics to CUCM.


Enhancements have been submitted for this behavior, Defect: CSCub07733


This defect CSCub07733 is fixed in CCM.12.5(1.10000.22).

Problem Details: We are getting alerted of a transcoder resource issue, but we are unable to pinpoint the exact reason why. Please see the attached logs and note regarding the sample call. Error "CallManager has run out of a transcoder resource with a list name: SYS-MRGL"
Subject: 629281 - OMC Transcoder Assistance Request
Sub Technology: Communications Manager Call Failure - IP Phone to IP Phone
Resolution Summary:
So from what I saw in the traces, there is an issue with the Region:


MediaConnect Request for CI (87907553, 87907569) in Regions (LAX-211-EOC-RGN,VM-CL1-SIP-TRUNK-RGN)

It?s terminating the call due to a mismatch in the capabilities, this is because the maximum allowed BW is 64 KBPs:

37622810.017 |17:29:07.608 |AppInfo  |DET-MediaManager-(216663)::preCheckCapabilities, caps mismatch! Xcoder Reqd. kbps(64), filtered A[capCount=2 (Cap,ptime)= (4,80) (2,80)], B[capCount=2 (Cap,ptime)= (11,20) (12,20)] allowMTP=0 numXcoderRequired=1 xcodingSide=1


Then it tries to allocate a MTP for such call:

Allocate XCoder from MRGL 6a1767a4-6da2-3e45-cb6f-6205f7b9b655 b/w regions SYS-RGN and LAX-211-EOC-RGN with caps 0x0 and mandatory caps 0x0 for CI 87907570
37622812.000 |17:29:07.614 |SdlSig   |MrmAllocateXcoderResourceReq           |waiting                        |MediaResourceManager(5,100,138,1) |MediaManager(5,100,140,216663)   |8,100,14,646614.427760^10.72.1.144^*     |[R:N-H:0,N:0,L:0,V:0,Z:0,D:0]  CI=87907570 MRGLPkid=6a1767a4-6da2-3e45-cb6f-6205f7b9b655 Kpbs=0 RegionA=SYS-RGN CapA=6 RegionB=LAX-211-EOC-RGN CapB=2 SuppressFlag=0 Type=1 DeviceCapablity= [0x0]0 MandatoryCapabilties= [0x0]0 Count=1



But is unable therefore the 503 is sent.

So to fix it we have two options:


  *   Add a MTP for the call
  *   Allow more bw for that region relationship.


CU wasn't available to reproduce the issue for over a month, closing the case and if the issue re-ocurrs re-open the case.

Problem Details: Hello, client wants to go to mixed mode and secure RTP for agent phones.  Client wants to leverage SRTP between CUBE to the agent phone for the entire media stream.  Is this configuration supported for UCCX 10.x through 12.x?
Subject: Need to confirm if TLS/SRTP Mixed Mode secure phones will work as Agent Phones
Sub Technology: UCCX/Contact Center Express/CRS - Finesse Agent Desktop
Resolution Summary:
3 questions asked by customer were answered:

Unfortunately, there is no support for SRTP in UCCX in any current version. The last information we have from our developers in 2019 is that SRTP support on UCCX CTI Ports is being evaluated for inclusion in 12.5. So, it?s on the radar and may be coming as early as 12.5 when it releases, but at this time there?s no guarantee that it will be included in that version.

If phone is registered to CUCM, using secure configuration and working, it will work fine with UCCX

UCCX does not support the CTI ports used by CUCM to make CTI secure, that is the only thing and if call arrives to phone, security icon is not displayed as it will appear when both devices are using security.

After that, customer became unresponsive, closing case as 3 strike due to lack of communication.

Hello we have a customer in the middle of a migration of one domain to another on different AD servers.  Our LDAP authentication is pointed at the old server and they are using a phased approach to move users from the old domain to the new domain.  The domains have no knowledge of each other currently. https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/voice-unified-communications/unified-communications-manager-version-80/111979-ucm-multi-forest-00.html
Subject: Customer on 2 different domains for LDAP Authentication
Sub Technology: Communications Manager LDAP Services (Sync, Authentication)
Resolution Summary:
No response after providing the following:



The usage of the Active Directory Lightweight Directory Service (AD LDS) is how we can authenticate to multiple domains. (Stated also in the LDAP Authentication section of the CUCM Admin Guide below)

When you are using the sAMAccountName value for the LDAP Attribute for User ID field, you can only authenticate with one LDAP Domain. To authenticate with multiple domains, you need to use the Active Directory Lightweight Directory Service (AD LDS).
 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/cucm/admin/10_0_1/ccmcfg/CUCM_BK_C95ABA82_00_admin-guide-100/CUCM_BK_C95ABA82_00_admin-guide-100_chapter_01110.html

Problem Details:
On Monday 13th we experienced a sudden drop of 50 calls  and we are trying to determine the root cause. When we tried to extract the CUCM Logs for sip traces, the active SUB only has CallLogs but no SDL traces, the SIP trace collection is enabled in Serviceability. 

After some review in our SBC connecting to the provider, we have a possble casue that calls were dropped because we stopped receiving audio from the carrier. And afer 20 seconds the call goes away. This was confirmed by our recordings.

So I need help in 2 things:
1. Help me investigating why CUCM is not giving me SDL traces and if there is a setting that makes a call to end when no RTP is received.
2. Is there a setting in the cube that also drop a call when RTP is not received?
Subject: Call log collections from CUCM and CUBE Settings
Sub Technology: Communications Manager PSTN/PBX Inbound/outbound Call Failure across Cisco Gateway (H.323, MGCP, SIP)
Resolution Summary:
The only explanation of a specific node not showing traces would be that that node was not running the Call Manager service.
Even so, this issue was related to RTP itself. Let's keep in mind RTP does not travel over CUCM, so we wouldn't see much in these aside from maybe calls being ended.

According to customer, provider stopped sending RTP for around 20 seconds.

Agreed to close this case.

Problem Details:
We configured the ECE datasource, and ECE stock reports, assigned the user permissions. However upon running the reports, could not see the Queues or users list.

UCCE 11.6
Finesse 12.0
CUIC 12.0
ECE 12.0
SSO Configured.
Simplex Environment.
Subject: CUIC 12.0 Reports to ECE 12.0 Chat and Email Not working
Sub Technology: UCCE/Contact Center Enterprise/ICM - Hosted Collaboration Solution (HCS)
Resolution Summary:
Summary of the incident

Issue:  CUIC 12.0 Reports to ECE 12.0 Chat and Email Not working

Root Cause: User's NT Service\SQLSERVERAGENT and NT Service\MSSQLSERVER on which SQL Server services are running were not added to the local group policy of the server in process level token on Reports DB.

Workaround: NA

Resolution: We've verified below checks -

1. Could see reports job is executing successfully. However, we don't see any data is populating in Reports DB.
2. Also, there are no any errors in EGMNT_ERRORS table.
3. On verifying the necessary permissions required for user NT Service\SQLSERVERAGENT and NT Service\MSSQLSERVER on which SQL Server Agent service is running we don't see both the user's are added to local group policy of the server in process level token. The application uses the functionality provided by the SQL Server Integration Services (SSIS) to allow customdata to be available for inclusion in custom reports. Note that custom data is not available in the reports that are included out-of-the-box.
4. Checked the status of the SSIS package (EG_DATA_COPY.dtsx) and were stuck in pending state.

To resolve the issue, we've performed below actions on AD Server and Reports DB -

1. Added both the users NT Service\SQLSERVERAGENT and NT Service\MSSQLSERVER  to local group policy of the server in process level token by following steps shared in our previous email.
2. Rebooted Database server to bring in above changes in effect.
3. Executed report job
4. Verified status of the SSIS package (EG_DATA_COPY.dtsx) by running the execution report and could see status of the package was succeeded.

After performing above actions, we could see data is populated in Reports DB successfully. We've tested by running the test reports from ECE reports console and from CUIC console as well and could see data is available in the reports.

When I check, usually there will be 1-3 active processes, and 2300+ sleeping processes/threads. Other UCCE engineers have reported that CSCva12312 was found in similar environments. We are seeking assistance with determining whether this bug is present, and the confirming the workaround/solution to the problem seen.
Subject: Solution Support: CUIC Subscriber alerting that thread count is exceeding 2000
Sub Technology: UCCE/Contact Center Enterprise/ICM - Reporting (CUIS, CUIC, WebView)
Resolution Summary:
++ Suggested performing the same WA as mentioned in the defect to increase the RisSystemAccessMaxProcessesThreads.

Defect: CSCva12312, CUIC Gives Warning of TotalProcessesAndThreadsExceeded
https://bst.cloudapps.cisco.com/bugsearch/bug/CSCva12312/?reffering_site=dumpcr


WorkAround: Execute the following steps to correct the threshold and stop the alarm.


++ Below query should give you the current configuration.

run sql select paramname,paramvalue from processconfig where paramname='RisSystemAccessMaxProcessesThreads'


++ Below will update the value.

run sql update processconfig set paramvalue='3000' where paramname = 'RisSystemAccessMaxProcessesThreads'


++ Restart "Cisco RIS Data Collector Service" after this change.

Subject: Unity Connection // No option no leave voicemail
Sub Technology: Unity Connection - Client Access (IMAP/ Visual/ Voicemail/ ViewMail)
Resolution Summary:
Issue 1 : Users were not able to leave the voicemail.
Sol: All calls to Unity Connection were directed to 'Attempt Sign-in'.
Checked the status on Unity connection port monitor- all direct calls
We checked the option 'Redirecting Diversion Header Delivery - Outbound' in the SIP trunk configuration."
This resolved the issue.

Issue 2: When retrieving the voicemails, the prompt would say incorrect username ?message from called party username instead of calling username?
Sol: ** On sip trunk to CUC, the caller ID was first redirecting number.Due to this CUC saw the call was From user Rizwanand also the VM was for rizwan.

We changed caller to originator and checked inbound redirecting header.This fixed the issue.

Problem Details:
Customer would like to change parameter from false to truth on Service parameter: display original calling number on transfer from cisco unity 
Making the change would have any impact?
Subject: Call manager // Service parameter question
Sub Technology: Communications Manager Admin and Web Page
Resolution Summary:
The parameter you mention changes the calling party for all calls received by CUCM registered IP Phones that receive a call coming from a Unity Voice Mail or a call transferred from Unity to an external number.

This is not a common scenario, since usually the one receiving the calls is the Unity system when users are leaving a Voice Mail, however, this could happen when Unity is configured with an AA greeting and/or making transfers to specific extensions on behalf of callers.

If set to True, the call received by the intended internal party will display the external caller?s ID.
If set to False, the call received by the intended internal party will display the Voice Mail port used by Unity to transfer the call to this user.

Resolution Summary:
1) For original error - Requested CUCM side logs + configuration to investigate further. 
Looks like user is able to login now, so issue is not reproducible.

2) There was another issue connecting to Voicemail server, which was due to Firewall. 
3) There was also Certificate Not Valid prompt upon each sign in. Cert was Imagicle used for contact search, worked on correcting that cert.
3) One more query customer raised: 
 Why jabber generating and picking up DefaultUser ? 
2020-01-20 09:16:20,898 INFO  [0x000000016eca7000] [overyConfigurationInterfaceImpl.cpp(168)] [service-discovery] [getVoiceServicesDomain] - Retrieved VoiceServicesDomain: kddiuc.com
2020-01-20 09:16:20,898 INFO  [0x000000016eca7000] [overyConfigurationInterfaceImpl.cpp(352)] [service-discovery] [isGeneratedDefaultUser] - userProfileEmailAddress : defaultuser@kddiuc.com result: 1

Though it's irrelevant to the issue and this email is not used to construct JID, customer is still curious. 
Found that it's used with EMM feature for mobile to push userid so that user doesn't have to enter it each time: 
 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/jabber/12_5/DIG_OnPrem/cjab_b_on-premises-deployment-cisco-jabber_125/cjab_b_on-premises-deployment-cisco-jabber_125_chapter_010000.html#CJAB_RF_M2B66F7A_00 

But there's nothing about Jabber populating this field with defaultuser@domain. Only found such behaviour for Jabber 4 windows with no UPN CSCuy69812 
Got response from BU:

?This default user is just used as the placeholder when UPN discovery is disabled. It is put into the ?last loaded? profile just so it is displayed as the default for the initial login. Once they login with any other ID, the last loaded profile will be changed.
It provides a default entry so the value isn?t empty, and shows what syntax is expected when you first enter a new value.?

So it?s there for initial login so value is not empty, that?s the use case for both mobile and Windows platforms.

Problem Details:
Hello Cisco TAC,

For our customer Rentokil we have encountered and issue where calls are hitting the wrong PQ, which seems to be caused by the ICM scripts using variables to get the PQ name together. When a call hits a script the script elements will use variables to finally get to the correct PQ name, which is then used as a variable with PQ select node.

It is as if the script uses information from a non related call to fill the variables, which should not be possible. Due to the variables being used in the script being incorrect for the handling of the specific call the call ends up on wrong agent. Think like an English inbound number variable get set as a Spain inbound number variable and hence the English call ending up at a Spanish speaking agent.

Our delivery engineer is currently working the clock round to get a workaround in place. We are only seeing this issue at the 11.6.2 ES7 release at the moment. We have a lot of other customers out there with similar script setup but on a different UCCE version where issue is not observed (UCCE 11.5.1 X and lower).

We do not have any UCCE 12.X customers yet, so we are not sure if the 12.X release train has this issue as well.

I still need to collect logs for this, so if you can let me know which logs are needed, please let me know. I was thinking script example file and rtr logs, but maybe I am missing something.

Cheers,

Edwin
Subject: Rentokil UCCE 11.6.2 ES7 - ICM scripting concatenation error for selecting PQ
Sub Technology: UCCE/Contact Center Enterprise/ICM - Central Controller (Call Router, Logger)
Resolution Summary: Persistent variables maintain their values between script invocations and hence they should be unique

Problem Details: CUCM 11.5.1.14900-11, phone 8851 upgrade to 12.6.1 (sip88xx.12-6-1-0101-692), even if the setting ''Always use prime line is disable, I'm not able to have the 2nd line selected by default
Subject: phone 8851 firmware 12.6 Always use prime line disable - don't works
Sub Technology: IP Phone with Communications Manager (except wireless)
Resolution Summary:
I found out that this will be expected behavior on 12.6.1 Firmware and later:

Revert to Primary Line in Session Line Mode
When a user is set up for Session line mode, the phone always uses the primary line for outgoing calls unless the user selects another line. If the user has calls on multiple lines, the calls are handled in sequence. When the last call ends, the phone reverts to the primary line.
You don't need to enable Revert to All Calls and Show All Calls on Primary Line for reversion to work.
                https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/cuipph/8800-series/firmware/12-6-1/releasenotes/p881_b_8800-release-notes-1261.html#CUIP_TP_N3753EF7_00


Field: Always Use Prime Line

This field specifies whether the primary line on an IP phone is chosen when a user goes off-hook. If this parameter is set to True, when a phone goes off-hook, the primary line is chosen and becomes the active line. Even if a call rings on the second line of the user, when the phone goes off-hook, it makes only the first line active. It does not answer the inbound call on the second line. In this case, the user must choose the second line to answer the call. The default value is set to False.

The purpose of the Always Use Prime Line field is very similar to the combination of Show All Calls on the Primary Line and Revert to All Calls when both of those two features are enabled. However, the main difference is that when Always Use Prime Line is enabled, inbound calls are not answered on the second line. Only dial tone is heard on the prime line. There are certain high call volume environments where this is the desired user experience. In general, it is best to leave this field disabled except for high call volume environments that require this feature.
https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/cuipph/8800-series/english/adminguide/P881_BK_C136782F_00_cisco-ip-phone-8800_series/P881_BK_C136782F_00_cisco-ip-phone-8811-8841_chapter_01011.html#reference_35EF4B7720E7A5F536BACFAEF2CE9356


If wanting to use the old behavior on firmware 12.6.1, then you can utilize the workaround below provided by the developers:


  *   On the Phone Configuration, fill with the BugID: CSCvp70780 in the "Customer Support Use" field

After the restart , we no longer seeing the issue related to Outofmemory or UnreachableDestination table.

To prevent outofmemory on native thread

  1.  We need to add XX:PermSize equal to -XX:MaxPermSize . This will prevent the call server to go outofmemory and do proper clean up permgen memory .


Step 1. Open the Regedit and navigate to the location Wow6432Node -> Apache Software Foundation -> Procrun 2.0 -> CallServer -> Parameters -> Java -> Options.
Step 2. Double click over Options or right click over Options and press modify.
Step 3. Append these values data box:

     -XX:PermSize=128m
     -XX:MaxPermSize=128m

 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/voice/call-routing-dial-plans/14074-in-dial-peer-match.html

Note: The maximum number of dial peers that can be configured on a Cisco IOS gateway depends on the available memory (DRAM). Each dial peer consumes approximately 6KB of memory. Make sure that you have at least 20% of the total memory reserved for other CPU processes. If the dial peers are used for call routing, a larger number of dial peers will add to the delay to route a call. This will be significant as the Cisco IOS voice stack looks through dial peers from the top down, similar to an Access Control List.

Problem Details:
CCE Version 11 (Base Version) installs JRE 1.7u51.

CVP component requires JRE1.7, but the last publically available 1.7 update is JRE1.7u80.

I raised a case previously to obtain latest JRE1.7 update (see  #687136582) and JRE1.7u231 was provided. There has since been a couple of further updates released, I believe u251 is the most recent. Can you please provide a copy of this so we can keep up-to-date security.
Subject: Latest JRE 1.7 update needed
Sub Technology: Unified CVP
Resolution Summary:
Shared the latest required java version jre1.7.0_251.
Steps to upgrade JRE

1. Copy the jre folder (inside the zip) to a known location on the Unified CVP Server. For example, C:\JRE.
2. Unzip JREUpdate.zip contents to a known location on your CVP Server. For example, C:\Cisco\CVP\bin. (this .zip should be inside your Cisco/CVP/bin folder).
3. To update the JRE version on the Unified CVP Server, run this script from the command prompt:
C:\Cisco\CVP\bin >JREUpdate.bat apply C:\JRE
4. The script executes and the CVP JRE gets updated to the new version. Ensure that the script output displays the updated JRE version.
5. The JREUpdate.bat script takes a backup of the old JRE on C:\Cisco\CVP\jre.old folder location. To revert to the previous backup version of JRE run this script from the command prompt:
C:\Cisco\CVP\bin>JREUpdate.bat revert
6. Note about JConsole tool: The CVP JRE contains JConsole tool. After successfully applying the new JRE update, the tool will be available inside the backup folder only: jre.old/bin. In case of any debugging needs, use the tool directly from within the backup folder.

Problem Details:
TTEC's customer, the US Census Bureau, has posed a question for which we need an answer.  In a Finesse server failover scenario in which an agent is in Wrapup state, when the agent desktop reconnects with the surviving Finesse server, how will the agent's state be handled.  Given the following conditions what will be the agent?s experience:
   ?	Conditions:
        o	UCCE 11.6(2) HCS 2000 Agents.
        o	2 Finesse server cluster (Side A Publisher and Side B Subscriber).
        o	Wrap up time set to 300 seconds in Agent Desk Settings.
        o	Agent?s desktop currently connected to the Side A Publisher when the failover occurs.
        o	Agent has been in Wrapup for 60 seconds when the failover occurs.
        o	It takes 60 seconds for the agent?s desktop to reconnect with the Side B Subscriber.
   ?	How will the agent's state be handled?
        o	The agent will be in Wrapup for another 240 seconds, OR 
        o	The agent be in Wrapup for 240 seconds minus the time it took for the agent's desktop to reconnect with 
                the surviving Finesse server (i.e. 240 ? 60 = 180 seconds), OR 
        o	Neither of the first 2 outcomes will be true, and the agent will in Ready.

Please provide the answer to this as soon as possible.  Thanks!

Problem Details:
Anil called in for TAC support. Trunk is down. Calls are not getting connected. Outbound calls impacted. No error messages. All users impacted in multiple sites Issue up for 3 hours. Nature of business: BPO.

Anil Yadav
gdcucassurance@team.telstra.com
+280449713
Subject: CUCM // Trunk down
Sub Technology: Communications Manager SIP Trunks
Resolution Summary:
Resolution Summary
*   SIP trunks namely LCT-CUCM-1-WIPRO-INDIA-2 and LCT-CUCM-1-WIPRO-INDIA were not in full service.
  *   We checked network connectivity towards the session targets 10.120.95.165 and 10.120.95.200 respectively from CUCM using ping and found that there were multiple packet drops (50 to 55% packet loss). This suggests that there is some network issue.
  *   Furthermore, we collected packet captures from CUCM to check the why the trunks are in down state. After checking the packet captures, we found that when the network is stable, CUCM is not receiving any reply to the OPTIONS keepalive message sent to the required destination IPs, thereby marking the trunk as down.
  *   All incoming and outgoing calls routed via the affected trunks are getting dropped by CUCM by 503 Service Unavailable error response.

Network connectivity was fixed and after that the SIP trunks were up.

Problem Details:
UsedDiskSpace : 61
MessageString : Common Disk utilization hits LWM! 
AppID : Cisco Log Partition Monitoring Tool ClusterID :  
NodeID : ghcarplacmpap01
 TimeStamp : Thu Jan 16 03:02:26 CST 2020. 
The alarm is generated on Thu Jan 16 03:02:26 CST 2020.

Wanted to know if there is a procedure to clean the disk or if that is needed.

Thanks

Kevin
Subject: Common Disk utilization hits LWM!
Sub Technology: Communications Manager Event Log Errors / Alarms
Resolution Summary:
This is event indicates that the percentage of used disk space in the log/common partition has exceeded the configured treshhold:

"LogPartitionLowWaterMarkExceeded

This event indicates that the percentage of used disk space in the log partition has exceeded the configured Low WaterMark.
The threshold percentage value of both of these events could be configured in RTMT based on the requirement . By Default High WaterMark is set to 95 % of total logging partition and Low WaterMark is set to 90% of total logging partition.

At times, need arises when there is insufficient space in the Logging Partition and additional space needs to be created for certain activity in call manager to take place. During such events additional space could be created in the Logging Partition, adjusting the threshold values of High WaterMark and LowWaterMark repectively.

When the threshold value of High WaterMark is lowered it would purge the older log files and this would create additional disk space in the logging partition. "

You can find furhte information and the procees to free some space in the following URL:


  *    https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/support/docs/unified-communications/unified-communications-manager-callmanager/200581-Procedure-to-Adjust-WaterMark-in-RTMT-of.html
  *    https://community.cisco.com/t5/unified-communications/cucm-how-to-lower-disk-usage-on-partitions/td-p/2983240

Cisco Unified CDM Deprecated Features

These features that are related to Cisco Unified CDM 8.x will not be available from Hosted Collaboration Solution release 12.5 and later:

    CUCDMSync functionality that provisions customer data from Cisco Unified CDM 8.x to SDR will not function.

    The Service Inventory reports that provide billing information based on Cisco Unified CDM 8.x cannot be generated.

    Note: If you have already generated the SI reports before upgrade, the reports remain intact. Post upgrade to HCM-F 12.5, you cannot generate the SI reports for Cisco Unified CDM 8.x.

    You cannot schedule and retrieve on-demand reports for Cisco Unified CDM 8.x application.

    You cannot add Cisco Unified CDM 8.x Management applications using the HCM-F 12.5 interface.

To summarize:
=============
There was no issue from CUCM perspective and no evidence of misbehavior ? it was sending all events for filtered call to Telisca CTI server, but didn't receive any response.
The root cause of ports unregistration ? connectivity loss between CCM/CTI services running on the server where ports are registered and Pub, to which telisca app talks.
Upon SDL link going back in service between Pub & Sub and devices registration status sync?ed, CUCM has sent DeviceInService / ProviderDeviceRegisteredWithLineInfoEvent  events to Telisca app.
Overall it was around 15 seconds of ?outage? from CUCM side (between CTI ports going out and in service).

So either IPSMA didn't get the messages or couldn't process them (JTAPI client issue or Telisca app issue).

Problem Details:
We have a CUCM cluster with two separate Expressway-C/E pairs connected for Internet calling.  The Expressways are configured identically except for IP address & certificate info that is specific to each Expressway.  The trunks to the Expressway-Cs are in a circular route group.  When placing a call from a video endpoint, calls to the first Expressway-C always result in a request terminated and the second Expressway-C handles the call.  If the call is routed to the second Expressway-C initially, it works fine.  This is particularly puzzling as the first Expressway-C/E was initially the ONLY Expressway pair in place and worked fine.  The second Expressway pair was added to the route group yesterday morning and tested OK at that time... that is calls were successfully being load balanced between the Expressway pairs.  However, yesterday afternoon the behavior with the first Expressway pair sending a 487 began, with no known configuration changes having been applied.  We have tried restarting all 4 Expressway VMs with no change in result.  In addition to the diagram, I am attaching diagnostic bundles from a test DX80 endpoint and all 4 Expressways, plus CUCM logs.  To illustrate the issue, I performed the following 4 test calls

8:35:29a EST - 7067901@attvideo.att.com to bd0170@attcorp-edge.webex.com - initially directed to Exp-CL2
8:35:45a EST - 7067901@attvideo.att.com to bd0170@attcorp-edge.webex.com - initially directed to Exp-CL1
8:36:06a EST - 7067901@attvideo.att.com to bd0170@attcorp-edge.webex.com - initially directed to Exp-CL2
8:36:21a EST - 7067901@attvideo.att.com to bd0170@attcorp-edge.webex.com - initially directed to Exp-CL1
Subject: Expressway Pair not Processing Calls Properly
Sub Technology: Expressway-C and E (Do not use for MRA or Collab Edge)
Resolution Summary:
What we can see in the logs is that the CUCM is tearing down the connection to CL1 cluster due to TLS issue:

98935227.003 |07:35:47.219 |AppInfo  |SIPD(34) - sendCloseOutboundConnection: mTsp.DeviceName[EXPC-CL1-Trunk] - Disconnecting call SIPCdpc(2,100,85,51403) on unsecure outbound TLS connection: 609570, peer addr=206.16.62.163

After that it sends a cancel to the Exp C and sends the call through the CL2:

98935247.001 |07:35:47.220 |AppInfo  |SIPTcp - wait_SdlSPISignal: Outgoing SIP TCP message to 206.16.62.163 on port 5061 index 609570
[247088455,NET]
CANCEL sip:bd0170@attcorp-edge.webex.com SIP/2.0
Via: SIP/2.0/TLS 206.19.41.161:5061;branch=z9hG4bK29cf214c3d048
Toggle Email

From: "Bryan Dooley" <sip:7067901@attvideo.att.com>;tag=84538823~b950b8e7-5a55-4fa7-8cf6-94d2da021f83-47373487
To: <sip:bd0170@attcorp-edge.webex.com>
Date: Wed, 22 Jan 2020 13:35:45 GMT
Call-ID: 163ad400-e2814fb1-26558b-a12913ce@206.19.41.161
User-Agent: Cisco-CUCM11.5
CSeq: 101 CANCEL
Max-Forwards: 70

When I looked at this screen, the issue jumped out at me, thanks to your question.  Apparently when creating the Security Profile for the second cluster, somewhere along the way I pasted the wrong subject name into the original profile.  When I corrected this to match the actual Expressway #1 certificate, my issue was resolved.

I know that I had to be missing something obvious, but I just didn?t see it until you told me that TLS failures were causing the behavior.

This resolves my issue and you can close this case.

Problem Details:
When a security scan is made against a customer, we get alarms triggered by the TIP service which is listening on the ICM call router. The customer does not have LIVE data server therefore the TIP service is not required.

I am trying to understand how to disable it and stop it from listening. The Serviceability guide mentions as an action "If TIP services are required, configure the proper TIP address/port and restart the node. If TIP services are not required, disable TIP in the registry."

But I cant find exactly what needs to be done in the registry. is it a matter of just removing the entries HKLM\SOFTWARE\Cisco Systems, Inc.\ICM\<cust>\RouterA\TIP\CurrentVersion\ListeningAddress, ListeningPort and TOSListeningPort and restarting the service? Please can you advise how to turn the TIP service off.

Thanks.
Subject: Disabling TIP Service
Sub Technology: UCCE/Contact Center Enterprise/ICM - Live Data Server
Resolution Summary:
The registry is under Router/CurrentVersion/TIP/Disable and PG/CurrentVersion/TIP/Disable, which, by default is set to ZERO, indicating NOT DISABLED ( So this would need to be set to 1 to disable)

A restart is required to cause it to take effect

Problem Details:
https://tools.cisco.com/security/center/content/CiscoSecurityAdvisory/cisco-sa-20161012-fin

Does this affect any of the Cisco applications? If yes, Is there a patch released for the same?
Subject: Regarding CSRF vulnerability in Cisco Applications
Sub Technology: UCCE/Contact Center Enterprise/ICM - Finesse Agent Desktop
Resolution Summary: Finesse is not a session-based web application in that it does not maintain any session IDs or cookies for an authenticated user.  Rather, Finesse relies on REST APIs that are authenticated on a per-request basis by inserting authentication headers into the HTTP request by means of supporting Finesse Javascript libraries.  The Finesse Javascript libraries are available only in the browser's runtime environment and cannot be used outside of this context to invoke a Cross-Site or Cross-Frame scripting attack.  Because of this, the only way to launch such an attack would be to do so while within an authenticated browser context.  Finesse is protected by use of the OWASP EASPI library

Problem Details: I am having an issue where Jabber clients are showing the CCMCIP server is connected to a server that I am not expecting it to talk to.  I would like to get more information how this selection is made.  We are running version 12.7.0 Jabber client and version 11.5.1 for IM&P and CUCM.
Subject: Jabber Showing Connected to the wrong CCMCIP server
Technology: Voice - Communications Manager Additional Apps and Plugins
Sub Technology: Jabber (Windows/Mac) - Features (Softphone, Desk Phone Control, Voicemail, URI Dialing, Desktop Sharing)
Resolution Summary:
If the client gets the _cisco-uds SRV record from a DNS query, it will automatically locate the user's home cluster & discover the services from that UDS query, two services the client discovers via UDS are the CCMCIP service and the TFTP service.

This means that Jabber will select the CCMIP and TFTP servers via the cisco-uds servers.

There are two options to be able to use which CCMCIP Profile will be used, it would be either using _cuplogin as Service Discovery, or using manual login pointing to an IM&Presence server, by doing that jabber will read the CCMCIP server configured in the IM and Presence server, under Application > Client Settings and Application > CCMCIP Profile.


 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/jabber/12_7/cjab_b_parameter-reference-guide-jabber-127/cjab_b_parameter-reference-guide-jabber-127_chapter_0101.html#CJAB_RF_C60DD1A1_00

Hi Team,

I a finding issue with the CUC digital networking .
Cisco Unity Connection version: 11.5.1.14900-11
Subject: CUC digital networking not working  " CUC home server not reachable"
Contact Customer Name: AT&T COMMUNICATION SERVICES INDIA PVT. L
Sub Technology: Unity Connection Digital Networking / VPIM
Resolution Summary:
-	Digital networking failing from CUCM Cl29 / Unity Cl16 to CUCM Cl28 / Unity CL15
-	From the Unity Logs we see we are getting a 404 Not Found on the INVITE to the route string 11115515
-	In the CUCM Logs we see we are coming inbound Cu1-VmIIGA-CL29-VMS-Trunk and failing digit analysis to route the call to 11115515
-	We checked and found that the partition applied to the route string 11115515 was not applied to the Inbound CSS on the Cu1-VmIIGA-CL29-VMS-Trunk
-	Once we added the partition to this CSS, the digital networking was successful

Problem Details: We have a CUCM cluster that was installed using the 7500 user OVA template. We need to increase the server size to support 10,000 users per server. I have tried to find documentation to support either method but nothing shows up with what is actually supported or required.
Subject: CUCM capacity change
Sub Technology: Communications Manager Install/Upgrade
Resolution Summary:
The recommendation is to use one of the following options:

  1.  Build a new set of VMs using the correct ova for the number of users you plan to support.
     *   Back up your current cluster.
     *   Restore in the newly built VMs.
     *   Decomission the old cluster.
  2.  Use PCD to create a migration task to new VMs using the correct ova for the number of users you plan to support.
     *   Let PCD do the heavy lifting for you.



Just modifying the virtualization details of the current VMs is not a supported solution in this scenario.

Resolution Summary:
During Troubleshooting we "created" additional extension entries in the CUCM DB.
This was done to test and confirm the overall call routing behaviors. 
to ensure a "clean environment" during our troubleshooting efforts, 
the "unneeded" extensions(due to partition mapping) were removed. 

After removal, we ensured the extensions werre correctly mapped to the affected Device. 
After this "cleaning" it was found/confirmed that call routing behaved as desired. 

While (as TAC) I am not away of any "database bugs" that created stale entries for a Line Group,
It seems this is the behavior that was encoutnered. 
The cleaning of the excess extensions allowed for CUCM to correctly update the DB Entries and route the call as desired. 

The Reason MOH was encoutnered appears to be more related to the Line Group (or something within the environment),
that had a "Native call queueing" or another value that would "queue" the call (with no one available this leads to MOH).
The "other" possibility could be related to the "Logged into Hunt Group" setting at the device level. 

----------
Additional partner testing further clarified that unexpected MOH trigger sourced from "Call Recording Server".
While I have not personally seen that type of behavior before partner was still okay with overall RCA.

Problem Details: Jabber MRA Login not working
Subject: Jabber MRA Login not working
Sub Technology: Collaboration Edge / Mobile and Remote Access (MRA)
Resolution Summary:
Provided the following action plan:


Step 1

Choose Cisco Unified CM IM and Presence Administration > Diagnostics > System Troubleshooter.

Step 2

Under Inter-clustering Troubleshooter, find the test Verify that each TLS-enabled inter-cluster peer has successfully exchanged security certificates and verify that is has passed.

Step 3

If the test shows an error, note the intercluster peer IP address; it should reference the cluster on which you uploaded the CA certificate(s). Continue with the following steps to resolve the issue.

Step 4

Choose Presence > Inter-Clustering and click the link associated with the intercluster peer that was identified on the System Troubleshooter page.

Step 5

Click Force Manual Sync.

Step 6

Allow 60 seconds for the Inter-cluster Peer Status panel to auto-refresh.

Step 7

Verify that the Certificate Status field shows "Connection is secure".

Step 8

If the Certificate Status field does not show "Connection is secure", restart the Cisco Intercluster Sync Agent service on the IM and Presence database publisher node and then repeat steps 5 to 7.

  *   To restart the service from the admin CLI run the following command: utils service restart Cisco Intercluster Sync Agent
  *   Alternatively, you can restart this service from the Cisco Unified IM and Presence Serviceability GUI.

Step 9

Verify that the Certificate Status now shows "Connection is secure". This means that intercluster syncing is correctly established between the clusters and that the CA certificates that you uploaded are synced to the other clusters.

Customer agreed to close this case

Problem Details:
Hello Team,

We are getting issue while registering 7940 and 7960 on our 11.5 CUCM.

Both type of phones giving error TFTP Authentication Errro.
Subject: TFTP Authentication Error
Sub Technology: Certificates (CTL, ITL, TVS, TLS, SRTP, eTokens, Agent Flow SSO, Secure Conferencing)
Resolution Summary:
From the CTL logs that you have uploaded, I can see that you are using a multi san certificate for the CCM+TFTP.
You only have publisher entry in the CTL file.

CN is ucsp01efra-ms.e-go07g0bqbb.businesstogether.orange-business.com

   CTL Record #:2
                  ----
BYTEPOS TAG             LENGTH  VALUE
------- ---             ------  -----
1       RECORDLENGTH    2       3278
2       DNSNAME         11      ucsp01efra
3       SUBJECTNAME     129     CN=ucsp01efra-ms.e-go07g0bqbb.businesstogether.orange-business.com;OU=UCaaS;O=Orange Business Services;L=Germany;ST=Germany;C=DE
4       FUNCTION        2       CCM+TFTP
5       ISSUERNAME      20      CN=RIOTINTOISSUING3
6       SERIALNUMBER    19      31:00:00:21:78:F7:4B:7C:1F:DA:8C:8F:50:00:05:00:00:21:78
7       PUBLICKEY       270
8       SIGNATURE       256
9       CERTIFICATE     2535    52 E5 63 8E 27 2A 8F 7E 54 69 44 E7 1A 30 DA BB D3 E2 E2 0D (SHA1 Hash HEX)
10      IPADDRESS       4       57.197.136.1


I found an enhancement raised for this issue which can be the root cause.

Symptom:

When generating a CTL File and using Multi-SAN certificates, it will only place 1 entry in the CTL file under CCM+TFTP for the Publisher node.
Due to this, devices that support Security by Default (ITL) will be required to reach out to TVS to verify the certificate of any node that is not the Publisher.
Devices that do not support Security by Default, will only be able to register with the Publisher node, and will fail registration with any other node.

You can refer to the bug:

 https://bst.cloudapps.cisco.com/bugsearch/bug/CSCuz76174

Action Plan:

++ 7940 and 7960 phones do not support Security by Default and you are using multisan certificates.

++Kindly try registering phones on publisher node and check once if the issue gets resolved.

Problem Details:
It has been brought to my attention that in March of this year, Microsoft is going to require LDAP channel binding and LDAP signing for Active Directory.  Since we use LDAP to authenticate when logging into CUCM, Unity, etc., what is needed to accommodate this change?  

Here is a link for the change I was given:
https://support.microsoft.com/en-us/help/4520412/2020-ldap-channel-binding-and-ldap-signing-requirement-for-windows
 
Let me know if there is any other information I need to provide.
Subject: Call Manager and LDAP
Sub Technology: Communications Manager LDAP Services (Sync, Authentication)
Resolution Summary:
CUCM uses an LDAP simple bind connection, so you need to use an SSL / TLS connection (that is, LDAPS) to connect to an AD server with LDAP signature enabled.
If you are using LDAP (non-SSL / TLS connection) with CUCM in the current environment, you need to switch to LDAPS (SSL / TLS connection) before applying the Windows update, if you are already using LDAPS there nothing more to do.

Resolution Summary:
Resolution Summary
*   We successfully uploaded tomcat multi-san cert on the CUCM cluster. We reloaded the nodes and once they came up, we checked that the certs are evenly distributed to all nodes and tomcat-trust as well. All the  phones got registered successfully as well.
  *   We disabled IMnP HA on CUCM and successfully uploaded the cup-xmpp cert on both the IMnP nodes. We reloaded the nodes and later confirmed that the required cert is under cup-xmpp-trust as well. We forgot to enable IMnP HA on CUCM. Please do so.
  *   We tried uploading CUC certs but we faced the mentioned error: ?CSR public key and Certificate public key do not match?. After investigating further, we found that that the CSR used to generate the certificate is old and is not matching with the current CSR available on CUC.
*   I advised you to use this new CSR (Downloaded from CUC PUB) to generate the certs from CA authority, upload it to CUC pub and sub, reload the nodes one by one and check the uploaded certs?s expiry date.
*   You informed that you have received the new cert from the customer. We uploaded this cert to CUC Pub and as it was Multi-SAN cert, this cert was installed on CUC Sub as well.
  *   We restarted the CUC Pub and Sub so the certificate install takes effect.
  *   We compared the old certs?s Public Key with new cert?s Public key and we could see the difference. That is the reason that we were facing cert upload failure earlier.
  *   Now the certs are successfully installed and everything is working as expected.

We have a small number of third party sip phones that are used for meeting room speakers/microphones.

Problem Details:
hi 

we are facing an issue on a new sip trunk deployement 
the telco says the trunk is up on his side but we see that on our side it's not and they says that they dont receive sip option
Subject: cisco cucm telco sip trunk issue
Sub Technology: Communications Manager SIP Trunks
Resolution Summary:
++ On a Webex with Saad, we tried to collect logs from RTMT but the app is unable to connect to the CUCM server. We collected the logs from CLI. Saad will open a separate SR to work on the RTMT issue.

++ From the logs we didn't see Outgoing SIP Options. Took a pcap and found 406 Options request from telco through UDP, while the CUCM was sending Re-transmissions through TCP.

++ We set UDP in the Sip Trunk Security Profile and reset the trunk. After that, the trunk shows Full service.

++ Ok to close.

Subject: Jabber for iPhone getting logged out automatically
Technology: Voice - Communications Manager Additional Apps and Plugins
Sub Technology: Jabber (Mobile Devices) - User Login
Resolution Summary:
As per the discussion with the BU engineer, this is expected and it should get fixed with the APNS deployment.
For doing so we will need to follow this document:

 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/cucm/push_notifications/cucm_b_push-notifications-deployment-guide.pdf

Alongside the proper versions needed.
Other than that we don't have any further workaround for the issue with the current versions that the customer has, they will need to upgrade to the recommended versions in the documentation.


After keeping investigating the latest PRT shared by Atul we find something really interesting. That matched the behavior you were saying and that you couldn?t reproduce in your lab.
The iPhone asking for the user to press the login button. During the past few days Colin and I were working on this to actually go through the very bottom of the situation and we have find the following:

The issue we are seeing on that iPhone It?s related to Local Authentication TouchID feature for iPhone.

What we are seeing is that the end user enabled TouchID, but authentication failed and get_edge_request got 401 error several times while login Jabber due to invalid credentials, so local authentication was treated as authenticate required (fast login disabled) and show sign-in screen while press Jabber icon.


There are two cases with Touch ID enabled
1. If authenticate failed due to invalid credentials, need to reauthenticate again while kill and relaunch Jabber.
2. If the customer do sign out and sign in Jabber manually, it needs to reauthenticate again.

So in order to configure it correctly you?ll need to do the following
1. input correct credentials in Jabber during login while enable Touch ID.
2. Do reauthenticate while press Jabber icon, and kill and relaunch again, it should work fine.

Or to have a quick fix you could disable Touch ID with the XML config key LocalAuthenticationWithBiometrics if you don?t want to go with the previously described behavior.


However we still recommend that the APNS needs to be deployed since we don?t know when Apple will decommission the Voice Sockets, and that will definitely impact your deployment, since that change can come at any given time and directly from Apple company. That?s why APNS is strongly recommended as best practice.
