Resolution Summary:
No response after providing the following:

----

As stated on the Webex, UPN is blocking the login:

2020-02-11 10:23:33,677 INFO  [0x00002410] [scovery\ServiceDiscoveryHandler.cpp(201)] [service-discovery] [CSFUnified::ServiceDiscoveryHandler::setupDiscoveryDomains] - *-----* Retrieved DNS Domain 'cwpanama.com' from 'Windows User Principal Name (UPN)'


Given that this is not the full domain of the cluster you are configuring, then we need to disable the UPN Discovery to allow the user to put in the proper User@domain.com<mailto:User@domain.com> to point the client to the proper DNS SRV records to reach the CUCM cluster. Via GPO / Installation this will be done with the following:

[cid:image002.jpg@01D5E1B3.9E76A970]
 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/jabber/11_0/CJAB_BK_D657A25F_00_deployment-installation-guide-jabber-110/CJAB_BK_D657A25F_00_deployment-installation-guide-jabber-110_chapter_01100.html


               ????? msiexec.exe /i CiscoJabberSetup.msi UPN_DISCOVERY_ENABLED=false EXCLUDED_SERVICES=WEBEX CLEAR=1

I added the EXCLUDED_SERVICES=WEBEX as well to avoid the initial attempt for Webex to ensure a smooth login attempt for the user.


For a per client basis, you can modify the bootstrap file with the following process for testing if wanting to avoid the proper installation process mentioned above:

1. Edit the Jabber-bootstrap.properties file found in "C:\ProgramData\Cisco Systems\Cisco Jabber"

2. Add entry: upnDiscoveryEnabled: false

3. Add entry: ServiceDiscoveryExcludedServices: WEBEX
4. Save the updated file
5. Exit Jabber completely from the Windows Notification Area (next to the clock)
6. Relaunch Jabber
7. Reset Jabber

Problem Details:
Consulting with our enterprise team and the consensus is that Cisco apps require Thick / Thick provisioning (EXAMPLE: Thick Provisioning on VM and Thick provisioning on the datastore). Some of our consultants were asking if Cisco apps have caveats where we could provision Thick/Thin (EXAMPLE: Thick provisioning for the VM and Thin provisioning for the datastore/array itself.).  There is discussion about leveraging this option for monthly cost savings.
I researched this and found this article that clearly sets guidelines for recommending Thick provisioning, but alludes to the option that Think provisioning can be supported, but disk space MUST be maintained in the array.
https://www.cisco.com/c/dam/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/uc_system/virtualization/collaboration-virtualization-hardware.html#largeTRC

Can you help us clarify, with documentation, whether Thick/Thin provisioning is a possible option, and whether it is even supported.  Please provide documents we can share with upper management to settle this design challenge, as we are currently in a holding pattern with changes and expansion plans until we can get this resolved.
Thanks,
Subject: Cisco UCS - datastore best practices - thin vs. thick provisioning
Sub Technology: Communications Manager Install/Upgrade

Resolution Summary: the inbound call has the survivability.tcl script enabled.  When that script is in control of the call, it takes control of the From and P-Asserted-ID and does not allow any override by a SIP profile.  The only way to make modifications that may work would be to use an inbound sip profile on the inbound dial-peer to make the change there.

Problem Details:
Release 11.5(3)
Build Number 11.5.3.10000-2
Deployment Mode HCM Standard
Platform Version 11.5.3-1521045619

Few of the local admin accounts for a customer have lost the information from all the fields.
We have tried to re-enter the information but it does not show anything even after saving it successfully.
Please help to get it back.
Subject: [VSR-19919] {273769958} || Byram || CUCDM not showing admin account fields.
Technology: Voice - Communications Manager Additional Apps and Plugins
Sub Technology: CUCDM 10.1.1 and above (Cisco Unified Communications Domain Manager) for HCS
Resolution Summary:
No response after providing the following:

---

See the latest from VOSS:


Grant Wilson took a look at the bug that Therodus raised and provided the following response:

The problem here is that the left model in the relation which is, HcsAdminUserDat, gets created correctly with space in the username. Eg: "User Test"
But the right model which is data/User gets created with the invalid space character replaced by an Underscore eg: "User_Test". The data/User model is where all of the Users details are stored which is why this appears blank as there is now no link between the left model and the right model as the join is done on the Username which no longer matches.

When the right model is created its using the following CFT in the workflow steps below:

Step 7 - Template (HcsAddUserCFT) before evaluation:
{
"username": "{{ fn.replace input.hcsUname, ,_ }}",



Step 7 - Template (HcsAddUserCFT) after evaluation:
{
"username": "User_Test",



In my opinion space should never be used in a Username and we should block input of this via a Regex in the Relation GUI rule as well as backend validation in the Data model in data/HcsAdminUserDat


For the time being ....

In the short term to fix this problem, VOSS can login with tdkadmin and modify the data/User model instances directly and add back the required space which has been replaced by the Underscores. Or alternatively modify the data/HcsAdminUserDat and replace the space with an Underscore.
               .
               .
               .

               VOSS L3 input:


Even though we can perform a workaround for the existing admins who have spaces, I would rather suggest deleting those and recreating them with no spaces.  As I mentioned on the troubleshooting call and per our developer, there should be no spaces when creating usernames.

I am trying to confirm if Regex will be adjusted to block the ability to create user names with spaces. Looking at the bug, it looks like spaces will not be allowed in our next release 20.1.1.

We should try to get out of this habit now because of this.

Let me know your thoughts. We can get on and take care of existing admins if there are issues with deleting/recreating but it should be pretty straightforward.


In short, we can either modify the Local Admins currently created, or delete and recreate these admins without spaces due to this will not be allowed in future releases anyways.

Problem Details:
UCM version 11.5.1.15900-18

When a PSTN  call comes in the system and hit the Auto Attendant, if the caller tries to get transfered, they will not ear ring back during the transfer. 

Call flow : PSTN PRI (581-824-0372) -> GTW SIP -> CUCM -> CUC -> can ear CUC -> REFER 3358 -> NO RING BACK -> AFTER 18 sec -> CUC VM Can ear

After looking at the trace, I see that CUCM request for an Annonciator but never sends the udp port to the GTW. Insteed I see that the CUCM sends to the GTW a m=audio 4000.

With a network capture to the GTW, I can confirm that the GTW receives the ringback on the correct port. It can just no be eared over the call.

I have found bug id CSCvc12634 wich mention a simillar scenario. It states that the workaround is using a late offer trunk for refered calls, but in this scenario, cucm already sends the INVITE late offer. It respons to the 200OK w/SDP of the GTW with an ACK that contains m=audio 4000.

CALL-ID of the example : 
As per CUCM
START : 14:52:23.671
END : 14:52:52.519

GTW to CUCM : E9F7E2EE-413E11EA-868BD462-E79CC30
CUCM to UNC : b22a7b00-e30190f7-7c5c36-bf04664
Phone 3358 TCP HANDLE : (3451665)
CUCM to UNC for VoiceMail of 3358 : c1112d80-e3019110-7c5c3e-bf04664

RTP PORT GTW to CUCM : 23904
RTP PORT CUCM to GTW : 24648, 24646, 24644, 24642
24644 is the RING BACK PORT for Annonciator

I would like a workaround or the fixed version since this issue is affecting all incoming call and causing grief to our customer.
Subject: No ringback on call transferred by Unity
Sub Technology: Communications Manager PSTN/PBX Inbound/outbound Call Failure across Cisco Gateway (H.323, MGCP, SIP)
Resolution Summary:
Enabling Duplex Streaming resolved the issue

Per the SRND:

In some installations, it might be a requirement to establish a two-way media connection with an annunciator. To enable this capability, set the Cisco Unified CM service parameter Duplex Streaming Enabled to True. This may be required for firewall transversal or possibly for SIP early-offer scenarios.
 https://www.cisco.com/c/en/us/td/docs/voice_ip_comm/cucm/srnd/collab11/collab11/media.html?bookSearch=true

Problem Details: We have had a lot of issues lately with reports taking a considerably long time running. I performed a show status and there are no signs of resource degradation. Please assist in determining why reports are taking so long to run.
Subject: CUIC Reports Long Delay After Running
Sub Technology: UCCX/Contact Center Express - CUIC Standalone Integration
Resolution Summary:
Problem was due to custom report.
It is being run against a 3rd party DB which queries the AWDB.
The custom report is querying tables that do not exist in AWDB.
The custom report was also querying these tables with no limit on time.
CUIC has a limit of 8k rows for historical and 3k rows for real time reports.

Problem Details:
Hello TAC,

We have a HCS client who we are hosting CUCM v 10.5.2 who is intermittently losing Directory services at various sites.  Restarting the tomcat service on the call manager often reestablishes the connections for a time but they drop out several times a year.  

Currently, the last tomcat restart did not correct this for all sites and so we are opening this case to see where we need to start investigating, what captures are needed and how to proceed as from the environment we can not seem to reproduce the issue with an IPC device.  They are losing directory services on both hardware and software endpoints.
Subject: Corporate directory services losing connection
Sub Technology: Communications Manager Event Log Errors / Alarms
Resolution Summary:
I explained customer:

I explained customer that based on my research for similar behavior of the error, phone model, CUCM version, workaround and others, everything points to an issue with failure of TVS certificate validation.

When it happens phones display the error message "Host Not Found" and it is related to bug CSCux21905: Cisco Unified Communications Manager Trust Verification Service Denial of Service Vulnerability.

Fixed in version: 10.5(2.14900.16) = 10.5(2)SU4.

His server is running CUCM 10.5.2.13901-2 =  10.5(2)SU3a

More details here: https://bst.cloudapps.cisco.com/bugsearch/bug/CSCux21905

In order to fix the issue we need:

dial-peer voice 209 voip
description Fax-line
translation-profile outgoing inbound
destination-pattern 9196825961
session protocol sipv2
session target ipv4:172.17.0.14
no voice-class sip early-offer forced
voice-class sip bind control source-interface GigabitEthernet0/2
voice-class sip bind media source-interface GigabitEthernet0/2
dtmf-relay rtp-nte
codec g711ulaw
no fax-relay sg3-to-g3
fax protocol pass-through g711ulaw
no vad
 
Calls are now working correctly.

29-Jan-2020|04:48:08.812|ERROR|Tomcat.stderr|main|              at 


## Cleared and performed re-indexing for the table in question. Further DB vaccum. 

1. Login to PCA CLI as root 
2. Go to /opt/emms/emsam/
3. Stop the PCA server /opt/emms/emsam/bin/cpcmcontrol.sh stop and wait for the command to complete
4. Start DB - /opt/emms/emsam/bin/start_db.sh
5. Change directory - cd /opt/postgres/9.2/
6. Load environment ? source pg92-openscg-cpcm.env
7. Delete all records from pg_statistic - /opt/postgres/9.2/bin/psql -p 5433 --username=cmuser  cpcm -c "DELETE FROM pg_statistic;"
8. Re-index table - /opt/postgres/9.2/bin/psql -p 5433 --username=cmuser  cpcm -c "REINDEX table pg_statistic;"
9. Run --  vacuumlo -U cmuser -p 5433 -v cpcm
10. Run - /opt/postgres/9.2/bin/psql -p 5433 --username=cmuser cpcm -c "VACUUM FULL VERBOSE ANALYZE;"
11. Run - /opt/postgres/9.2/bin/psql -p 5433 --username=qovr qovr -c "VACUUM FULL VERBOSE ANALYZE;"
12. Stop DB - /opt/emms/emsam/bin/shutdown_db.sh
13. Start all Processes - /opt/emms/emsam/bin/cpcmcontrol.sh start

Problem Details:
This is in regard to routing of traffic from HCS through the Miami Cubes to PSTN. Currently, we are seeing the calls hit the Cube/router, but the pstn is seeing the call without audio or incorrect codec.

See call flow below that we are trying to resolve:
HCS phone -> CUCM -> Cube -> PSTN

Please reach out to Griffith Taylor for more details: griffith.taylor@cwc.com
Mobile number: 868-224-2249 or 868-313-3974 (Trinidad Number)
Subject: CWC-Issue with the calls
Sub Technology: Communications Manager PSTN/PBX Inbound/outbound Call Failure across Cisco Gateway (H.323, MGCP, SIP)
Resolution Summary:
Activities with the previous engineer (jpaizjaim).

As CU is moving configuration from old system to new one, calls through UCCE cluster are working correctly, however, from HCS cluster, they are not.

HCS/CUCM<>CUBE<>Provider, all SIP

Initially, we  started troubleshooting the outbound calls.

We verified the call was matching the incorrect dial-peers.

we were matching dial-peer 200 as incoming from CUCM and 103 as outgoing to provider.

Taking care of them, the 200 was not the correct one from CUCM, it should be matching 101 or 109.

We modified dial-peers in order to match via URI.

We tested and it was not working yet.

We verified, and found we are sending audio, video and app capabilities, which could be possibly causing an issue with provider side.


Focusing, on calls with dead air, we were going to verify the statistics, as it seems the jabber we are using is not being reached fro the correct interface.

After it, CU complained, all site was down.

***Problem 2, incoming calls stared to fail.


With TS, provider stated we were creating a loop, we verified, and it was matched dial-peer for outgoing side, instead of CUCM, to provider again. We changed destination pattern from some dial-peers, and calls are working now.

***Coming back to outbound calls, we will force audio only.


We are currently using dial-peer 102, as outgoing to provider and 109 as incoming from CUCM.


After:

voice service voip
sip
audio forced


Calls are still facing no audio. We verified and jabber seems to be not reachable through correct interface. CU is using VPN


CU tested from deskphones, and calls are working.

Now, they are working on extension to extension calls.


We are currently in a webex session troubleshooting calls from to webex:

Calling number: 7006
Called number: 1-868-224-2249


We are matching incorrect dial-peer, incoming 109 and outgoing 103. We should match 101 as incoming, in order to use GiEth0/0/1.45 interface for media.
We did a matching via URI for 101.

We tested and it seems to be intermittent yet. Current call example:
from:
1-868-313-3974

2020-01-31 11:37:01,675 ERROR [0x00003a1c] [ents\ecc\src\config\PhoneConfig.cpp(778)] [csf.ecc] [csf::ecc::SoftphoneConfig::parse] - Parse: sipProfile/sipLines missing

AWDB Failover
The prerequisites for AWDB failover are as follows:


The secondary Administrative Workstation Database (AWDB) is configured.
The secondary AWDB host is configured through the Finesse administration console.
Finesse can connect to the secondary AWDB host.
The Distributor service is running on the secondary AWDB host.

Agents and supervisors are authenticated against the AWDB database. When an agent or supervisor makes a successful API request (such as a sign-in request or call control request), the credentials are cached in Finesse for 30 minutes from the time of the request. After a user is authenticated, that user continues to be authenticated until 30 minutes pass, even if both AWDBs are down. Finesse attempts to reauthenticate the user against the AWDB only after the cache expires.

Problem Details:
Title
CUCM / LBG ? EMEA / Silent calls on 8841s when using EMCC

END CUSTOMER DETAILS 
End customer Name: LBG
Platform: EU/INDIA/APAC/US: EU
FAULT DETAILS
BT fault reference number: TAS000010116784
Business Impact: Medium 
PROBLEM DESCRIPTION:
Customer has reported intermittent, yet regular, silent calls when dialling out using their Cisco 8841. The users in question are using Extn Mobility cross cluster and they also have call recording enabled. There is a detailed description of what exactly is happening below between the chevrons << >>. This detail below has been provied from Ravi Pal Singh. He said that something similar was investigated and solved before, but because this now involves EMCC, it?s another issue. What we would like to know if there is any other way of making this work without disabling Call Recording or upgrading CUCM? These are unfortunately not options for this customer currently.

<<<< 
As discussed, the issue here is quite similar to an old issue reported last year for LBG that relates to Jabber/SIP devices with call recording enabled . ( TAS000007419964) 

Jabber/SIP devices by default send all the codecs in the INVITE to CUCM . When CUCM receives this INVITE , it uses the same codec order that it receives from the SIP Client to create an outbound INVITE. This is because of the parameter in SIP Profile ?Accept Audio Codec Preferences in Received Offer? which as part of HCS design we have set to ON . In the previous case and this one ,  the phone is sending the codec order as ?0 8 116 18 101? i.e ulaw first and then alaw. CUCM leaf cluster uses the same codec order and sends the INVITE to SME , SME then forwards it on to SDIN. SDIN negotiate G711ulaw which is negotiated all the way back to the phone. 
As the phone has call recording enabled, CUCM Leaf Cluster sends re-INVITEs to both the phone and the SME so new recording streams can be established from the phone BiB. This is where the issue happens. In response to the re-INVITE from the SME , SDIN this time replies back with g711alaw instead of ulaw , which the SME forwards to CUCM LC and LC to the phone . However as the phone has already negotiated ulaw for recording it cannot change to alaw and sends a ?488 not acceptable media? . 

To resolve this a new SIP profile LBG Standard SIP Profile was created that had the ?Accept Audio Codec Preferences in Received Offer? set to OFF . This profile was applied to all Jabber devices and SIP phones on the Leaf Clusters . Unfortunately, this change will not work for SIP devices that log into a remote cluster . EMCC devices, as you know, do not register directly but appear as ?remotely logged in? devices on the home cluster. The remotely logged in devices use a different Database table whereas the CUCM makes use of a different DB entry to map a device with it?s assigned SIP profile. Therefore, the CUCM is not able to apply an EMCC SIP Profile to the remotely logged in device.

I took Suman?s help to test this in the NAL and unfortunately we couldn?t get this to work despite trying a lot of things . The SIP profile for an EMCC based phone is picked up from the EMCC template and we tried changing the profile on the template , changing the global service parameter , creating new users , updating all templates but none of it worked . Having checked internally, it appears that this was an issue with older CUCM releases i.e 10.5.2 and the way this works has been changed from CUCM 11.5 onwards . I am not sure what LBG?s upgrade plans are . I am aware the RAM/firmware upgrades for them have kicked off , but not sure if the UC APPs would be upgraded anytime soon.

Problem Details: After we switched the IM Address scheme to the Directory URI field, our directory is not working.  I have modified the jabber xml file to the settings which I think are correct, but could not get it to work.
Subject: Jabber for Windows Directory Not Working after to switching to Flexible JID
Technology: Voice - Communications Manager Additional Apps and Plugins
Sub Technology: Jabber (Windows/Mac) - Directory Contact Sources/Resolution
Resolution Summary:
checked logs and we see its a bad search filter:
[csf::person::ldap::LdapSearcher::search] - searchScope=2, filter=(objectClass=userProxyFull(|(sAMAccountName=ben.barr)(mail=ben.barr@encova.com))), baseDN=OU=Associates,OU=Accounts,DC=Enterprise,DC=LDAP, ldap=(1D55F828)
[csf::person::ldap::LdapSearcher::search] - Ldap search error. rc= -7, msg=Bad search filter. ldap=(1D55F828)

changed the base search filter to: (&(|(objectclass=userProxyFull)(objectclass=contact)))
it works
also (&(objectclass=userProxyFull)) works
it looks like we needed the "(&" at the start of the search filter because jabber is putting the base search filter infront of the search base to create one big filter
